reviews.text: Baron with barely any facilities worth mentioning and barest in terms of seating and shelter, it's not a very good station overall. Trains only stop here every half an hour most of the time. Assuming they aren't delayed of course which if that is the case good luck.
Good station with less population and pollution

Trains here arrive very infrequently as it is a very unused station. This makes it quite hard to travel to and from. There are no departure boards which can be frustrating as you don't know when the trains come. Ticket machines are often broken which can hinder your travel. I have been to the station a few times and had not seen a member of staff yet which is very disappointing.

Much of the station looks run-down. The path to get to the station is hard to find and narrow. There is no public transport to the surrounding area from the station so you may have difficulties getting to other places.
It's a nice Map showing the area
No bathroom facilities or disabled (or any elevator) access.
